ion to the United Nations after the war, and his role in the American Zionist movement. From Cohen’s life and work, Lasser draws important insights into the development of the New Deal and the evolution of postwar liberalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAvocatsxBiographiesxÉtats-Unis. 0aHommes d'ÉtatxBiographiesxÉtats-Unis. 0aIntellectualsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aIntellectualszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aIntellectuelsxBiographiesxÉtats-Unis. 0aLawyersxBiographyxUnited States. 0aLawyerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aLiberalismxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aLiberalismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aLibéralismexHistoirex20e sièclexÉtats-Unis. 0aNew Deal, 1933-1939. 0aNew Deal. 0aStatesmenxBiographyxUnited States. 0aStatesmenzUnited StatesvBiography. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aLeone, Richard C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlesinger, Arthur M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012888840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300128888423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300128888/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles